By Chris Swaim ,
16 hours ago Sunny skies will carry us into the weekend! Our nice stretch continues and we will even add a warm-up into the mix with temps pushing 80Â° Saturday and Sunday. There will be a weak cold front come through late Sunday into Monday. A few models try to hold on to enough moisture to shake out a shower or two, but it doesn't look like much. Either way we will clear back out next week. We are facing a big temperatures drop with highs back in the low 60s!
